    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Retry Patterns Matter in Agentic Systems"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agentic pipelines call LLMs, external APIs, databases, and search engines. Every one of these can fail transiently: a rate-limit response, a momentary network timeout, a temporary service outage. Without a retry strategy, a single transient error terminates the entire pipeline. With a well-designed retry policy, the agent recovers automatically and the user sees no disruption."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The challenge is distinguishing retryable errors (transient, worth retrying) from permanent errors (wrong API key, malformed request, business logic failure) that retrying will never fix. Retrying a permanent error wastes time and tokens."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Exponential backoff retry: attempts with increasing wait times between failures"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Exponential Backoff with Jitter"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The standard retry algorithm waits progressively longer between attempts (exponential backoff) and adds a random offset (jitter) to prevent all clients retrying at the same instant after a shared outage."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import time\nimport random\nimport logging\nfrom typing import Callable, TypeVar\n\nT = TypeVar(\"T\")\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"retry\")\n\ndef retry_with_backoff(\n    fn: Callable[[], T],\n    max_attempts: int = 4,\n    base_delay: float = 1.0,\n    max_delay: float = 30.0,\n    jitter_fraction: float = 0.2,\n    retryable: Callable[[Exception], bool] = lambda _: True,\n) -> T:\n    last_exc = None\n    for attempt in range(max_attempts):\n        try:\n            return fn()\n        except Exception as exc:\n            if not retryable(exc):\n                raise  # permanent error — do not retry\n            last_exc = exc\n            if attempt == max_attempts - 1:\n                break\n            delay = min(base_delay * (2 ** attempt), max_delay)\n            jitter = delay * jitter_fraction * (random.random() * 2 - 1)\n            wait = max(0.0, delay + jitter)\n            logger.warning(\n                \"Retrying after error\",\n                extra={\"attempt\": attempt + 1, \"wait_s\": round(wait, 2), \"error\": str(exc)},\n            )\n            time.sleep(wait)\n    raise last_exc\n\n# Example: retry an LLM call\nfrom langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\nllm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-sonnet-5\")\n\nresponse = retry_with_backoff(\n    fn=lambda: llm.invoke(\"Summarise the key points of the attached document.\"),\n    max_attempts=4,\n    base_delay=1.0,\n)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Identifying Retryable vs Non-Retryable Errors"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Classify errors before deciding whether to retry. HTTP status codes and exception types are the primary signals."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\nimport httpx\n\ndef is_retryable(exc: Exception) -> bool:\n    # Anthropic rate limit or server error\n    if isinstance(exc, anthropic.RateLimitError):\n        return True\n    if isinstance(exc, anthropic.APIStatusError) and exc.status_code in {429, 500, 502, 503, 529}:\n        return True\n    if isinstance(exc, anthropic.APIConnectionError):\n        return True\n    # Generic network errors\n    if isinstance(exc, (httpx.ConnectTimeout, httpx.ReadTimeout)):\n        return True\n    # Non-retryable: authentication, bad request, not found\n    if isinstance(exc, (anthropic.AuthenticationError, anthropic.BadRequestError)):\n        return False\n    # Conservative default: retry unknown errors once\n    return True\n\nresponse = retry_with_backoff(\n    fn=lambda: llm.invoke(\"What is the capital of France?\"),\n    retryable=is_retryable,\n)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Never retry a 400 Bad Request or 401 Unauthorized — these indicate a bug in your code or credentials. Retrying them burns tokens and delays surfacing the real error."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using LangChain's Built-in Retry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LangChain runnables expose with_retry() which wraps the retryable error filter and backoff logic without manual implementation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\nfrom langchain_core.runnables import RunnableConfig\nimport anthropic\n\nllm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-sonnet-5\")\n\n# with_retry applies exponential backoff automatically\nretrying_llm = llm.with_retry(\n    retry_if_exception_type=(\n        anthropic.RateLimitError,\n        anthropic.APIConnectionError,\n        anthropic.APIStatusError,\n    ),\n    wait_exponential_jitter=True,\n    stop_after_attempt=4,\n)\n\n# Use exactly like the base llm — retries are transparent\nresponse = retrying_llm.invoke(\"Explain idempotency in REST APIs.\")\n\n# Chain-level retry: wraps any step in the chain\nfrom langchain_core.runnables import RunnableLambda\n\ndef unstable_retriever(query: str) -> list[str]:\n    return vector_store.similarity_search(query)  # may throw transiently\n\nsafe_retriever = RunnableLambda(unstable_retriever).with_retry(\n    retry_if_exception_type=(ConnectionError, TimeoutError),\n    stop_after_attempt=3,\n)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retry in LangGraph Nodes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In a LangGraph graph, wrap the retryable operation inside the node function. The node either succeeds and returns a state update, or exhausts its retry budget and returns an error signal that a conditional edge can route to an error handler."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from typing import TypedDict, Literal\nfrom langgraph.graph import StateGraph, END\n\nclass PipelineState(TypedDict):\n    query: str\n    result: str\n    error: str\n    retry_count: int\n\ndef call_llm_node(state: PipelineState) -> dict:\n    try:\n        response = retry_with_backoff(\n            fn=lambda: llm.invoke(state[\"query\"]),\n            max_attempts=3,\n            retryable=is_retryable,\n        )\n        return {\"result\": response.content, \"error\": \"\"}\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return {\"error\": str(exc), \"result\": \"\"}\n\ndef route_after_llm(state: PipelineState) -> Literal[\"success_handler\", \"error_handler\"]:\n    return \"error_handler\" if state.get(\"error\") else \"success_handler\"\n\ndef success_handler(state: PipelineState) -> dict:\n    return {\"result\": f\"Processed: {state['result']}\"}\n\ndef error_handler(state: PipelineState) -> dict:\n    logger.error(\"LLM call failed after all retries\", extra={\"error\": state[\"error\"]})\n    return {\"result\": \"Service temporarily unavailable. Please try again later.\"}\n\nbuilder = StateGraph(PipelineState)\nbuilder.add_node(\"call_llm\", call_llm_node)\nbuilder.add_node(\"success_handler\", success_handler)\nbuilder.add_node(\"error_handler\", error_handler)\nbuilder.set_entry_point(\"call_llm\")\nbuilder.add_conditional_edges(\"call_llm\", route_after_llm)\nbuilder.add_edge(\"success_handler\", END)\nbuilder.add_edge(\"error_handler\", END)\ngraph = builder.compile()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Async Retry for High-Throughput Pipelines"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nimport random\n\nasync def async_retry(\n    coro_fn,\n    max_attempts: int = 4,\n    base_delay: float = 1.0,\n    max_delay: float = 30.0,\n):\n    last_exc = None\n    for attempt in range(max_attempts):\n        try:\n            return await coro_fn()\n        except Exception as exc:\n            if not is_retryable(exc):\n                raise\n            last_exc = exc\n            if attempt < max_attempts - 1:\n                delay = min(base_delay * (2 ** attempt), max_delay)\n                jitter = delay * 0.2 * (random.random() * 2 - 1)\n                await asyncio.sleep(max(0.0, delay + jitter))\n    raise last_exc\n\n# Fan-out with per-item retry\nasync def process_batch(queries: list[str]) -> list[str]:\n    async def process_one(q: str) -> str:\n        response = await async_retry(\n            lambda: async_llm.ainvoke(q),\n            max_attempts=3,\n        )\n        return response.content\n\n    results = await asyncio.gather(\n        *[process_one(q) for q in queries],\n        return_exceptions=True,\n    )\n    # Filter out items that failed all retries\n    return [r for r in results if not isinstance(r, Exception)]"
          }
        ]
      },
