      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Respecting the Retry-After Header"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When an API returns a 429 rate-limit response, it often includes a Retry-After header specifying how many seconds to wait. Honouring this header is more efficient than a fixed backoff: you wait exactly as long as needed, no more."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\nimport time\n\ndef retry_with_retry_after(fn, max_attempts: int = 4) -> any:\n    for attempt in range(max_attempts):\n        try:\n            return fn()\n        except anthropic.RateLimitError as exc:\n            if attempt == max_attempts - 1:\n                raise\n            # Anthropic embeds the wait time in the exception headers\n            headers = getattr(exc.response, \"headers\", {})\n            retry_after = float(headers.get(\"retry-after\", 0))\n            if retry_after > 0:\n                time.sleep(retry_after + 0.5)   # small buffer\n            else:\n                # Fall back to exponential backoff if header is absent\n                time.sleep(min(2 ** attempt, 30))\n        except Exception as exc:\n            if attempt == max_attempts - 1:\n                raise\n            time.sleep(min(2 ** attempt, 30))"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retry Budgets for Multi-Step Pipelines"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In a pipeline with N sequential steps, each with its own retry budget, the worst-case latency can grow large. A global retry budget caps the total retry time across all steps in a single run."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nimport time\n\n@dataclass\nclass RetryBudget:\n    total_seconds: float\n    _start: float = field(default_factory=time.monotonic)\n\n    @property\n    def remaining(self) -> float:\n        return max(0.0, self.total_seconds - (time.monotonic() - self._start))\n\n    def sleep_if_allowed(self, seconds: float) -> bool:\n        if self.remaining < seconds:\n            return False   # not enough budget — abort retry\n        time.sleep(seconds)\n        return True\n\nbudget = RetryBudget(total_seconds=30.0)\n\ndef retry_with_budget(fn, budget: RetryBudget, base_delay: float = 1.0):\n    attempt = 0\n    while True:\n        try:\n            return fn()\n        except Exception as exc:\n            if not is_retryable(exc):\n                raise\n            delay = min(base_delay * (2 ** attempt), budget.remaining)\n            if not budget.sleep_if_allowed(delay):\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"Retry budget exhausted after {attempt+1} attempts\") from exc\n            attempt += 1"
          }
        ]
      },
