          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retry patterns are a first line of defense against transient failures in agentic pipelines. Use exponential backoff with jitter to spread retries over time, and always classify errors before retrying — permanent errors like authentication failures or bad requests should never be retried. LangChain's with_retry() covers most LLM call retry needs; wrap it around individual nodes in LangGraph and route on the error field to separate graceful recovery from hard failures. Test retry logic with mocked transient errors to verify both the happy path and the exhausted-budget path."
          }
        ]
      }
